Class Description
App
Starts the whole application, making the necessary beginning steps.
CancelReservationMessage
Sent when an attempt to cancel a reservation is made.
Controller
Acts upon the model and view and keeps them separate by controlling the data that flows into the model and updating the view whenever data changes.
CreateNewCustomerMessage
Sent when an attempt to create a new customer is made.
CreateNewReservationMessage
Sent when an attempt to create a new reservation is made.
Customer
A class modeling a customer in a hotel reservation system.
CustomerLoginScreen
Defines the screen the user will see when logging in as a customer.
CustomerMenuScreen
Defines the screen the user will see after successfully logging in as a customer.

Defines the screen the user will see when creating a new reservation as a customer.
CustomerScreen
Defines the screen the user will see after choosing to view the application as a customer.
CustomerSignUpScreen
Defines the screen the user will see when trying to create a customer account.
CustomerTest
Tests the Customer class.
CustomerViewReservationScreen
Defines the screen the user will see when viewing reservations as a customer.
DatePeriod

DatePeriodTest
Tests the DatePeriod class.
Discount
A class modeling a discount for a reservation.
DiscountTest
Tests the Discount class.
EmployeeScreen
Defines the screen an employee will see.
HotelSystem
A class modeling the hotel reservation system itself, mostly how it handles customers.

Tests the HotelSystem class.
LoginAsCustomerMessage

LoginCustomerMessage

LoginScreen

LuxuryAmenities

LuxuryAmenitiesTest
Tests the LuxuryAmenities class.
Message
Interface allowing queue of messages to accept a message of any type.
NormalReservation
A class modeling a normal reservation at the hotel.
Reservation
An interface allowing for the ArrayList of reservations to contain any type of reservation.
ValveResponse
Declares the different types of responses a valve may send.
ViewReservationListMessage
Sent whenever an attempt is made by a customer to view his or her reservations.
